<p>Multiple people were stabbed on a London-bound passenger train on Saturday evening near Huntingdon in Cambridgeshire; authorities say ten people were taken to hospital, nine with life‑threatening injuries, and two men were arrested at the scene . British Transport Police said counter‑terrorism officers are supporting the probe while police work to establish motive and identities; officials have urged the public to avoid speculation as investigations continue . Prime Minister Keir Starmer condemned the &quot;appalling incident&quot; and thanked emergency services for their response .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/5gjU6RjC7AVS8Doe56MSHQW0mv1GcDCTP3M98zCfwfdwiQif3QbUDvyDtVZbkyxaWHQWL-n2zCkLFxBerKPsb4XmBxlzIw4XMYqBNx9LVj2aRQyJwCNz-xUdUL07Lao871tFSt3_Qmv_DZEcVQh38g7oS0GZwFs_yNgWM7TsKOCgo75_7q_d1pUl91pmYb8jv8vhf0R57X87GrPHJ7LeQ0xqBIGMSxLlbzegQ5UaqB1_w6dH6z_FCa7zhwG8pUC6eDcT3rJ-_Teqz5_48w' alt='Emergency personnel inspect a train at Huntingdon station after people were stabbed, Nov. 1, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Major incident: Police declared a major incident after ambulances and armed units were sent to the scene, with the response triggered around 7:40pm local time on Saturday</li><li>Scene reports: Several eyewitnesses described &#x27;extremely bloodied&#x27; passengers fleeing and social‑media videos captured a heavy police presence at Huntingdon station</li><li>Terror inquiry: Counter‑terrorism officers are supporting the investigation while defence officials said early indications suggest the incident may have been isolated, and a terrorism alert that was briefly declared was later rescinded</li><li>Arrests made: Armed officers stopped the train at Huntingdon where two men were arrested and taken into custody while a number of injured passengers were transferred to hospitals nearby</li></ul><blockquote>My thoughts are with all those affected - Prime Minister Keir Starmer</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Prime Minister Keir Starmer: He condemned the &quot;appalling incident&quot; and thanked emergency services, saying his thoughts were with those affected. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627248-uk-stabbing-attack-train/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Home Secretary Shabana Mahmood: She said she was &quot;deeply saddened&quot; and urged the public to avoid comment and speculation at this early stage. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627248-uk-stabbing-attack-train/'>RT</a>)</li><li>UK defence secretary: He said early indications point to an &quot;isolated attack,&quot; while stressing investigations were ongoing. (<a href='https://www.ft.com/content/b8240a58-8b1b-46be-b31c-2b6b1d2731ea'>Financial Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/627248-uk-stabbing-attack-train/'>Multiple people stabbed on UK train</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/live/2025/nov/02/cambridgeshire-train-stabbing-life-threatening-injuries-arrests-latest-updates'>Cambridgeshire train stabbing: police briefing expected after 10 injured in mass attack – latest updates</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20251102-uk-police-arrest-two-after-multiple-people-stabbed-on-train'>UK police arrest two suspects in mass train stabbing that leaves 10 wounded</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/uk-train-stabbings-injure-nine-police-arrest-two-suspects'>10 injured after stabbing rampage on British train; 2 men arrested</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/b8240a58-8b1b-46be-b31c-2b6b1d2731ea'>Two arrested after mass stabbing on train in Cambridgeshire</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.npr.org/2025/11/02/nx-s1-5594754/10-people-hospitalized-after-uk-train-stabbing-attack-9-with-life-threatening-injuries'>10 people hospitalized after UK train stabbing attack, 9 with life-threatening injuries</a> - npr.org</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/u